{
  "stem": "9168.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had the feeling that the judges tried very hard to be especially fair for this reason, and I felt, even bend over backwards in their judgments and in their sentences.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I do not remember distinctly the particular charges against the doctors who were acquitted.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I felt that it was because they may not have had direct-- direct participation in these experiments, but may have been kind of in positions where they were ordered to do minor preparatory work on the victims.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I really don't know, Gary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that was-- as we court reporters did not really know what went on in their-- the judges' deliberations-- any more than we know in a multi-judge tribunal today, or the Supreme Court, for example.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We made-- I made eye contact.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, occasionally they would look at us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And especially-- especially Karl Brandt.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I would not look at him as I walked by him, because I had seen him leering at another woman reporter as she walked by him, a very attractive blond woman who was older.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, we walked by them so close.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were so close to them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean closely walking by them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I just made a point of not, as I walked by him, and he was right on that corner, within arm's reach as I walked by, after I saw the way he looked at the other-- the one woman.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But sitting across from them listening, it's the same feeling that I had years and years later, all through the years, as I-- as an official court reporter in the Denver district court system here in murder trials.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Listen to the testimony, and then would look at the defendant on just a pause.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
